When the good folks at @nikesb asked me to design the Olympic Federation Kits, so many memories and feelings flashed through my mind. 
There have always been contests in skating, some took it super serious and some joked around, but most of us hung out, watched, talked shit and were interested in the skills and styles of the skaters entering the contest. I even rode my bike for 10 hours from The Netherlands to Germany to go see all the International Pro's in the M√ºnster contest back in the early 90's

Skateboarding is so extremely and insanely difficult to learn, it takes years and years and thousands of hard slams to even be an average skater.
Just imagine putting so much time and effort into it and getting so good you can compete at an Olympic level, that's insane... i take a deep bow for everyone that will make it in there this summer. 
Skateboarding shaped my life in such a positive way and i just hope that some kids somewhere that never even thought of skateboarding get inspired and fall in love with it by seeing it on the Olympics.

For those that are interested there is a little interview from me  on the @nikesb site, the link is in the thingy up there
